Despite a sand storm Friday, attendees at Burning Man continued to participate in the Nevada arts festival.

The 'Burners' were photographed moving their bicycles and walking through the festival grounds while wearing bandanas to cover their faces from the dust by the Associated Press.

One attendee, however, appeared relaxed while sitting underneath a beauty salon chair while a bicyclist rode past trying to escape the dust in a photograph from the wire service.

Similarly, another man at Burning Man was snapped with his arms behind his head while sitting in a beach chair during the storm.

Another snap showed a child on top of a structure that read 'Dust Happens.'

