The dust storm enveloped much of the view of the festival on Friday, though the giant burning man figure, along with a Ferris wheel, peeked out in photographs taken by Sasha Maslov.

Attendees were also captured by checking out multiple structures and sites on the festival grounds - including a giant boat in the desert and the so-called 'Temple of Grace' - by Reuters.

On Friday morning, a project almost 12 months in the making called Embrace - a 72-foot wooden sculpture of two people lovingly looking into each other, built across studios in Vancouver and Portland - was reduced to nothing but dust and ash.

